abstract: WASHINGTON — Troy Price, the Iowa Democratic Party chairman, apologized for the Monday night debacle that led to a 20-hour delay in reporting results from the Iowa caucuses and said his party released results from 62 percent of precincts on Tuesday.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Troy Price, the Iowa Democratic Party chairman, apologized for the Monday night debacle that led to a 20-hour delay in reporting results from the Iowa caucuses and said his party released results from 62 percent of precincts on Tuesday.

abstract: A first wave of results showed Pete Buttigieg and Bernie Sanders with an early lead, with Joseph R. Biden Jr. well behind.
snippet: A first wave of results showed Pete Buttigieg and Bernie Sanders with an early lead, with Joseph R. Biden Jr. well behind.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Democratic officials in Iowa on Tuesday provided a measure of clarity to the muddled outcome of its statewide caucuses, releasing a delayed first wave of partial results that showed Pete Buttigieg and Senator Bernie Sanders with a preliminary lead and former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. falling well behind the other top-tier candidates.

abstract: Amid a chaotic caucus night and speculation that a phone app was to blame for the delay in distributing results, Andrew Yang, the Democratic presidential candidate and former tech entrepreneur, offered an unsolicited thought.

abstract: The Iowa Democratic Party released partial results of its kickoff presidential caucus after a daylong delay late Tuesday showing former Midwestern mayor Pete Buttigieg with a slight lead over progressive Vermont Sen. Bernie Sanders in the opening contest of the party's 2020 primary season.
snippet: The Iowa Democratic Party released partial results of its kickoff presidential caucus after a daylong delay late Tuesday showing former Midwestern mayor Pete Buttigieg with a slight lead over progressive Vermont Sen. Bernie Sanders in the opening ...
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa — The Iowa Democratic Party released partial results of its kickoff presidential caucus after a daylong delay late Tuesday showing former Midwestern mayor Pete Buttigieg with a slight lead over progressive Vermont Sen. Bernie Sanders in the opening contest of the party's 2020 primary season.
headline_main: Buttigieg Slightly Leading Sanders in Partial Iowa Results
headline_print_headline: Buttigieg Slightly Leading Sanders in Partial Iowa Results

abstract: As MSNBC's Katy Tur wandered through a gym in Des Moines during her network's coverage of the Iowa caucuses Monday, she found a voter wearing a Bernie Sanders button sitting with supporters of Amy Klobuchar.
snippet: As MSNBC's Katy Tur wandered through a gym in Des Moines during her network's coverage of the Iowa caucuses Monday, she found a voter wearing a Bernie Sanders button sitting with supporters of Amy Klobuchar.
lead_paragraph: NEW YORK — As MSNBC's Katy Tur wandered through a gym in Des Moines during her network's coverage of the Iowa caucuses Monday, she found a voter wearing a Bernie Sanders button sitting with supporters of Amy Klobuchar.
headline_main: Iowa a Carnival of Democracy for Media — Until It Went Sour
headline_print_headline: Iowa a Carnival of Democracy for Media — Until It Went Sour

abstract: While the final results of the Iowa caucuses were unclear, there was no shortage of drama inside the Johnston Middle School gymnasium.
snippet: While the final results of the Iowa caucuses were unclear, there was no shortage of drama inside the Johnston Middle School gymnasium.
lead_paragraph: JOHNSTON, Iowa — For weeks undecided Iowans have been saying that they may make their decision based on the last candidate they see in person. On Monday night, that sentiment paid off for Senator Amy Klobuchar of Minnesota at Johnston Middle School.
